"""
fish_analyzer/gui.py
====================
Layer 5: Graphical User Interface

This module contains the EnhancedFishAnalyzer class - the main application window.
It's built with tkinter, Python's built-in GUI toolkit.

TKINTER CONCEPTS FOR BEGINNERS:

WIDGETS - Everything visible is a "widget":
   - tk.Label: Displays text
   - tk.Button: Clickable button (command= specifies what happens on click)
   - tk.Entry: Text input field (use StringVar to read/write value)
   - tk.Listbox: Scrollable list of items
   - ttk.Notebook: Tabbed interface
   - ttk.Frame: Container to organize other widgets

LAYOUT - How widgets are arranged:
   - pack(): Stack widgets (side="left"/"right"/"top"/"bottom")
   - grid(): Place in row/column grid (row=0, column=1, etc.)
   - fill="both", expand=True: Make widget resize with window

VARIABLES - Special tkinter variables that auto-update widgets:
   - tk.StringVar(): For text values
   - tk.IntVar(): For integers
   - tk.BooleanVar(): For checkboxes
   - Use .get() to read, .set() to write

APPLICATION STRUCTURE:
   The main window has a Notebook (tabbed interface) with 4 tabs:
   1. Data Setup & Calibration - Load files, set units
   2. Individual Analysis - Per-fish metrics and plots
   3. Shoaling Analysis - Group behavior metrics
   4. Spatial Analysis - Thigmotaxis and heatmaps
"""

